<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9200, 9300 AND 9400 SERIES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s11010k" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5117K" date="03/01/1996">
        <title>CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9200, 9300 AND 9400 SERIES</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The clutch control linkage consists of the clutch pedal, pedal shaft, release lever and
                        control rod connected through a bellcrank to the relay rod and the release shaft lever (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1101001">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1101001" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1101001" filename="../figg11/G1101001.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Typical Relay-Style Clutch Control Linkage Assembly</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. CLUTCH RELEASE LEVER</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. SPACER</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. BRACKET BEARING, SPRING WASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CLUTCH PEDAL SHAFT</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. CLUTCH PEDAL RETURN SPRING</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. CLUTCH PEDAL</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. RELEASE SHAFT LEVER</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. CLUTCH RELAY ROD</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. CLUTCH RELAY BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>10. BELLCRANK</callout1>
                            <callout1>11. CLUTCH CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>OPERATION</title>
                    <para>Vehicles with manual transmissions have a clutch pedal which, through the clutch linkage, is
                        used to engage or disengage the clutch. With the clutch pedal released, the clutch is engaged,
                        driving the transmission and rear wheels. With the pedal pressed, the clutch is released,
                        permitting selection of transmission gear changes.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
